cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.CV

This paper deals with the robustness of Deep Learning-based network traffic classification against adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also extensively uses Deep Learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper deals with network traffic, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
